
[1]blight

   BLIGHT, n.

   1. A disease incident to plants, affecting them variously. sometimes
   the whole plant perishes; sometimes only the leaves and blossoms, which
   will shrivel, as if scorched.

   2. Any thing nipping or blasting.

    In America, I have often heard a cutaneous eruption on the human skin
                       called by the name of blights.

     BLIGHT, v.t. To affect with blight; to blast; to prevent growth,and
                          fertility; to frustrate.
